<a href="#1" id="1">(See Hansson [6].)</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">An operation ∘ on a belief set K is a relational descriptor revision if and only if there is a set {a mathematical formula}X of belief sets with {a mathematical formula}K ∈ X (its outcome set),{sup:2} and a relation ≦ on {a mathematical formula}X, such that (i) {a mathematical formula}K ≦ X for all {a mathematical formula}X ∈ X, and (ii) for all descriptors Ψ : {a mathematical formula}K ∘ Ψ is the unique ≦ -minimal element of {a mathematical formula}X that satisfies Ψ , unless Ψ is unsatisfiable within {a mathematical formula}X, in which case {a mathematical formula}K ∘ Ψ =K.</a>
